Global Cytomegalovirus Immune Globulin Intravenous Human (CMV-IGIV) Market Insights
Cytomegalovirus Immune Globulin Intravenous Human (CMV-IGIV) Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 1.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.2% from 2024 to 2030.

Cytomegalovirus Immune Globulin Intravenous Human (CMV-IGIV) Market Overview
The global market for Cytomegalovirus Immune Globulin Intravenous Human (CMV-IGIV) was valued at USD 1.8 billion in 2023, and it is projected to reach USD 3.2 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.2%. This market expansion is attributed to the rising demand for effective immunoglobulin therapies, particularly in the treatment of CMV infections in immunocompromised patients, including transplant recipients. The key applications of CMV-IGIV include preventing and treating viral infections in patients undergoing organ transplantation and those with congenital cytomegalovirus infection. With an increasing global focus on healthcare and advancements in biotechnology, the market is anticipated to grow steadily in the coming years.

